cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.AI 

This paper discusses optimization algorithms for min-max games, which are commonly used in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses mathematical tools such as the Schur theorem, indicating that it may belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses optimization techniques, suggesting it may also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
